    "summary": "LOOK ACROSS BORDERS \n\nThat\u2019s what I do by nature. For inspiration, new ideas and digital opportunities for todays challenges. I look across borders of profession, market and culture. Bringing people of various disciplines together to develop strategic and creative solutions. Thereby bridging borders between business, technology and design. My routine is to stay up-to-date in digital trends, innovations and todays customer behaviour. I have extensive experience in e-commerce, online branding, marketing and communication for clients in various industries, B2C and B2B. But always from a point of view like Albert Einstein said; \"Imagination is more important than knowledge\".\u00a0\n\nPersonal profile & professional ambition\nCreative mind, analytical approach and  good social and communication skills.  Initiator, team player, generalist and optimist. Curious, unconventional, convincing, decisive and reliable. \n\nCurrently (2020) working as Lecturer Digital Marketing at the International Business School in Rotterdam. Creative leadership of teams and coaching of (young) professionals. Lecturing in the field of online strategy, digital marketing and branding.\n\nMaybe later would like to work again on the development and implementation of digital innovations and creative ways of working within a (international) company or digital agency. ",
